[ctns_make id='LF-SlopeFormulaS']

    [ctns_front]
Slope Formula<br>Linear Function
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The <strong>slope</strong> of a linear function is the ratio
$|\frac{y_2-y_1}{x_2-x_1}=\frac{\Delta y}{\Delta x}|$
for two points $$(x_2,y_2)$$ and $$(x_1,y_1)$$ on the graph of the linear function.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]
